==English==

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|en|leprosy|otic}}, q.v.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Of or [[related]] to the [[disease]] [[leprosy]].

====Usage notes====
Generally, the adjective {{m|en|leprous}} is used when speaking of people afflicted with the disease, its symptoms, or its transmission and ''leprotic'' is prefered when speaking of the disease itself.

